(firstQuint)A Study of Fluconazole in the Treatment of Fungal Infections of the Throat in Patients With Weakened Immune Systems.

 Patients receive fluconazole oral suspension for a minimum of 3 weeks and maximum of 8 weeks.

 Patients are evaluated weekly, and treatment continues for 2 weeks after resolution of symptoms.

 Endoscopic exams and possibly biopsies are performed at baseline and at the end of treatment.

 Patients undergo follow-up at 2 weeks post-treatment.

